sentences: Eladia Blázquez (February 24, 1931 – August 31, 2005) was an Argentine tango singer and composer.
In 1970, she recorded her first tango record and fought against the macho spirit that dominated tango.
She was named Hija dilecta de la ciudad de Avellaneda in 1988 and Illustrious Citizen of Buenos Aires in 1992.

Blasquez received the Premio Konex Award in 1995 and 2005, both for being the best lyricist and composer of tango for the preceding decade in Argentina.

Blasquez died on August 31, 2005, in the Clínica Bazterrica in Buenos Aires, age 74, from cancer.
